The Government's Decisions:

Under the Disability Inclusive Education Scheme (Secondary Level), special educators will provide education to the differently abled. The expenditure "Demand No. E-2,2202 General Education, 01 Primary Education, 106 - Teachers and Other Services, (00) (00) (01) Samagra Shiksha Abhiyan (General) (State Share Wo Percentage) (2202 I 612) (Programme), 31 - Subsidiary Grants (Non-Payment) "to be shared from the budgetary provision available in these financial years 2024-25.

3. The Director of Education (Primary), Maharashtra State, Pune shall credit the funds required to adjust the amount borrowed from Pradhan Mantri Poshan Shakti Nirman Yojana Cell, Pune to the Pradhan Mantri Poshan Shakti Nirman Yojana Cell, Pune.

4. The Director of Education (Primary), Maharashtra State, Pune shall credit the amount of the stipend to the account of the respective Special Teachers. Make sure that the salary amount is credited to the account of the particular teacher concerned. If a teacher's name is found twice, it should be ensured that the salary is paid only once in such a case. The Director of Education (Primary), Maharashtra State, Pune will be held responsible if it is found that excess salary has been paid.

If the said Special Teachers have been paid salary earlier for the period September, 2024 to March, 2025 in pursuance of any court case, the balance amount shall be paid by adjusting the amount from the amount admissible by way of consideration as mentioned in paragraph 2 of the said Government Judgment. A bond of payment of salary paid to the special teachers shall be drawn from the concerned special teacher at the time of payment of salary subject to the final decision to be taken at the government level regarding the adjustment of such teachers.

6. Submit a report to the Government if funds are left over after payment of salary as mentioned above. Prior approval of the government should be taken before appropriating the balance. The utilization certificate of the funds disbursed should be submitted to the government within a period of one month.

The funds are being handed over to the State Project Director of Education, Maharashtra Council of Elementary Education, Mumbai. The Under Secretary / Cell Officer (Cash Branch / Accounts Branch), Department of School Education & Training, Mantralaya, Mumbai is being declared as the "Drawing and Disbursing Officer" and the Joint Secretary / Deputy Secretary, Department of School Education & Training, Mantralaya, Mumbai as the "Controlling Officer" for the collection and disbursement of these funds. The concerned Drawing and Disbursing Officer shall draw the funds from the treasury and deposit them in the SNA account of the State Project Director, Maharashtra State Primary Council, Mumbai.
